      "id": "2022Mains_26JulEvening_Chem_Q4",
      "year": 2022,
      "paper": "26JulEvening",
      "question_number": 4,
      "question_text": "At 30°C, the half life for the decomposition of AB₂ is 200 s and is independent of the initial concentration of AB₂. The time required for 80% of the AB₂ to decompose is (Given: log 2 = 0.30, log 3 = 0.48)",
      "question_type": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "topic": "Physical Chemistry - Chemical Kinetics",
      "sub_topic": "First order kinetics - half life",
      "correct_answer": "C",
      "solution_summary": "Half-life independent of concentration → first order reaction. k = ln2/t₁/₂ = 0.693/200. For 80% decomposition, 20% remains. t = (1/k)ln(1/0.2) = (200/0.693) × ln5 = 200 × 2.333 = 467 s.",
      "concepts_required": [
        "CK_09",
        "CK_10",
        "CK_12"
